Hi all<br>
<br>
I just started a level 30 berserker on galahad with a level 30 shaman bot. I always played Albion on Palomides, but have been getting more and more bored with Albion.<br>
<br>
Now to my question, I noticed that the damage my berserker puts out isnt too shabby at all. It sure beats paladin damage and it looks like its as good if not better than what a mercenary can dish out. Is the outrage of the berserker community mostly because everyone has their damage reduced by 40% or is it really that a berserker cant compare to mercenaries and blademasters, the Light Tank counterpart of Albion and Hibernia?<br>
<br>
I am not here to start a flame or insult any berserkers. I seriously want to know why berserkers are considered to be swinging wet noodles when (from my very limited experience) a level 30 berserker seems to do okay.<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Ev <p>------------------------------------------------<br>
